CONDA

1. Check if Conda exits (if it doesn’t, go to step 2. If it does, go to step 3)
conda --version

2. Install Miniconda

Download Miniconda installer (Linux version)
wget https://repo.anaconda.com/miniconda/Miniconda3-latest-Linux-x86_64.sh

Run the installer
bash Miniconda3-latest-Linux-x86_64.sh

3. Configure Conda channels
Add main community channel (scientific computing packages)
conda config --add channels conda-forge

Add bioinformatics-specific channel (FastQC, samtools, etc.)
conda config --add channels bioconda

Ensure Conda prioritises channels strictly (prevents conflicts)
conda config --set channel_priority strict

4. Create a clean isolated environment for bioinformatics
conda create -n vibrio python=3.10 -y

5. Initialise Conda in the shell
Set up Conda so "conda activate" works in terminal
conda init

6. Reload shell configuration so changes take effect immediately
source ~/.bashrc

7. Activate the environment (switch into it)
conda activate vibrio

8. Install tools
Install FastQC (quality control tool for sequencing data)
conda install fastqc -y
conda install trimmomatic -y 
conda install multiqc -y
conda install bwa -y
conda install samtools -y
conda install snippy -y
conda install iqtree -y 
conda install unicycler -y

9. Check what environment exists and tools
conda env list
conda list

10. Export environment  
conda env export > vibrio_environment.yml

11. Add to GitHub repo
git init
git add vibrio_environment.yml
git commit -m "add vibrio cholera analysis environment"
git remote add origin https://github.com/JolynneM/bioinformatics-cli-lab.git
git branch -M main
git push -u origin main


